annotation.TEXT: Ah, so here's where this music that we briefly heard in the music room last time actually plays.
Oh, come on. I was totally high enough to get onto that pipe. (It always bothers me that I can potentially jump six tiles high, but not every time, due to the way Mario's running speed oscillates.)
Jammed coin count: 3
DOUBLE KILL!
Yay, a useless flower.
Yeah, not happening. At least not around here.
Gotta check every pipe... Wait, these aren't pipes! Well, I'll check 'em anyway!
Unfortunately, I end up forgetting to come back for those coins way up there, and that's gonna bother my OCD...
BGM: Little Nemo: The Dream Master (NES) - Mushroom Forest
DOUBLE KILL!

Wow, so I guess this is a literal ludicrous speed bonus game! ...Oh, crap! Why is the video ending now?! It wasn't supposed to end quite yet! D'OH! Well, be sure to read the video description, guys. To be continued...
I'm glad there are blue duders here. Otherwise, I'd probably have to say "Bye, Yoshi" there!
Looks like this P-switch is only reachable with tongue power!
Oh, man. I didn't know if this was a bottomless pit down here or not, and I actually fell by accident. Fortunately, it's perfectly safe down here.
Wow, that was fast! Yellow wins!
Green shell = Electricave. Yellow shell = Apple Jungle. First to get a 1-up wins!
Jammed coin count: 4
Goal tape average so far: 110 / 3 = 36.667 stars each.
Gulp!
Hi, Yoshi!

Brilliant! Well, at least I'm still regular super, which I guess is because there's no reserve item in this hack. Honestly, I prefer the regular power up system with the reserve item most of the time.
That silly berry facial expression.
Ha! I totally saw that coming!
Hello, and welcome back to Something else! The "else" is lowercase but the "Something" isn't, so that means "Something" has got to be important! Now, let's head into Dinosaur Land here...
Oh, what's this? Hey, what's with my bonus star counter?
Silly koopas and their silly shells that look like Yoshi heads. I guess this is why this level is called "Dinosaur Land".
Unfortunately, it looks like I have to go back in order to climb back up.
Bonus game average so far: 4.68 / 1 = 4.68 1-ups each. (Each coin counts as 0.01 towards this, of course.)
Goal tape average so far: 70 / 2 = 35 stars each.
COINS!!!
Nuts. I guess the wall is just plain too high. Oh, well. I had to try.
Ehh, I guess I'll do the pink berry bonus cloud thing.
Whoa, is that an apple?
Looks like I see the theme of this level. Man, if only I had fireballs...
Aw, nuts. I should've recycled the P-switch.
Gulp! So much for the blue shell...
Wow, a star?! That's way more awesome than just a measly 1-up!
And I got another coin jammed. Sure, why not?
Aw, no greeting message? Oh, well. At least it seems that Yoshi is happy to see me!
Whoops! Oh, well. Nuts to that coin. Also, these are the real pipes that I should be checking!
DOUBLE KILL!
Zwee!
So, that means I'm headed to Apple Jungle!
Aww, how sweet♥.
Oh, yes! It's the music that goes with practically everything!
BGM: SMB3 - P-switch
Alright, gimme my 1-up... What?!
BGM: CUSTOM - Decisive Here We Go
BURN! BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! BURN! WOO! BURN TO THE GROUND! TRI-FORMATION! BURN! BURN! BURN TO THE GROUND! WOO! WOO! BURN!
Push!
Toasty!
WHOOOAAA!!!!!
Nuts. Failed to get three double kills in a row. And I fell down again, too.
And, of course, everyone knows that blue shells are made of Red Bull, because they give Yoshi wings! ...Oh, man. Take a close look at this berry while it's a sprite! LOL!
We have Electricave, and Apple Jungle. Now, how will I decide which one to play next?
Zwee!
Yeah, I guess these blocks are unbreakable, even though they appear cracked.
Nope, just 40. Oh, well. It's still more than enough to send me to the bonus game.
BGM: Street Fighter II - Guile's Theme
I don't know why I'm bothering to check there...
I'm farticus! No, I'm farticus!
Alright, let's feed Yoshi some Poké Puffs... Er, I mean berries. (I wonder what it would be like if you could interact with Yoshi in Pokémon-Amie...)
Oh, I couldn't have shell jumped over that wall anyway, because there's a ceiling.
Munchers, eh? Well, this route just begs for me to take Yoshi down it!
Yay! Fireballs! Now I can start yelling out Flame Hyenard lines again!
And I'm still checking these pieces of land that may as well be pipes...
I wonder if I can get a stomping combo going...

Now, here I'm really thinking that there's nothing but pit down below. However, I checked back later, and it turned out that I was wrong. There is solid land down there, along with a springboard for me to get back up. (And a ? block on the ground that I'd probably need a cape to hit.)
And, that's it for this level. Can I get a 50 here?
BGM: Zelda: Oracle of Ages/Seasons - Rush for Maple's Items!
Huh, I wonder-- Whoa, hello there hidden 1-up! Now, as I was about to say... I wonder if I can shell jump over this wall...
10-life combo!
Whoa, those coins sure are happy.
Darn. Didn't get them all... Oh, well. Let's finish the level.

Aww... I don't get to keep Yoshi when I leave the level... Also, what's this? I was expecting a red level to appear there, but that's not the case. Instead, I've unlocked two levels at once, and can go to either one.
